\title{metaLong: Longitudinal Meta-Analysis with Robust Inference and Sensitivity Analysis}
\description{
\code{metaLong} provides a coherent workflow for synthesising evidence from studies
that report outcomes at multiple follow-up time points.  The package covers:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Pooling}: \code{ml_meta()} fits a random-effects or fixed-effects model at each
time point using robust variance estimation (RVE) and optional Tipton
small-sample corrections via \code{clubSandwich}.
\item \strong{Sensitivity}: \code{ml_sens()} computes the time-varying Impact Threshold for a
Confounding Variable (ITCV), both raw and significance-adjusted.
\item \strong{Benchmark calibration}: \code{ml_benchmark()} regresses each observed study-level
covariate and compares its partial correlation against the ITCV threshold.
\item \strong{Nonlinear time trends}: \code{ml_spline()} fits natural-cubic-spline meta-regression
over follow-up time with pointwise confidence bands.
\item \strong{Fragility}: \code{ml_fragility()} computes leave-one-out and leave-k-out fragility
indices across the trajectory.
\item \strong{Visualisation}: \code{ml_plot()} and S3 \code{plot()} methods produce publication-ready
trajectory, sensitivity, and benchmark figures.
}
}
